    <string name="measurement_help_title">Signal measurements</string>
    <string name="measurement_help_body">RSRP (dBm)\nReceived signal power. Less negative is better.\n\nRSRQ (dB)\nSignal quality compared with interference and load. Less negative is better.\n\nSINR (dB)\nSignal-to-noise ratio. Higher is better.\n\nGNSS\nThis value drops as the latest location fix  becomes less useful for matching the signal sample. A smaller ± accuracy value and a newer fix are better.</string>
